{"session_id":"svc-1778557903130879133","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-12T03:51:45.166067031Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"gpt-5.4-mini","sticky":{"key_present":true,"bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"requested_harness":"codex","resolved_harness":"codex","harness_source":"request_harness","requested_model":"gpt-5.4-mini","resolved_model":"gpt-5.4-mini","work_dir":"/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-fcdbc731-20260512T035137-c0bdf98c","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Too big if any holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across ~5+ files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children once more; third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;`.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260512T035137-c0bdf98c/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing child IDs, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a success. Do not mix implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260512T035137-c0bdf98c/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;`.ddx/executions/20260512T035137-c0bdf98c/no_changes_rationale.txt` must contain one:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` reject.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;To request orchestrator decomposition, add `orchestrator_action: decompose` alongside `status: open`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260512T035137-c0bdf98c/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260512T035137-c0bdf98c/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and project defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-fcdbc731\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003eprompts: tighten shared blocks; add FEAT-022 guardrail-list comment block; add invariant tests\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;Both execute-bead prompt strings (Claude: 1078 words, Agent: 1020 words) contain prose paragraphs that consume more tokens than equivalent bullet checklists. 19 load-bearing guardrails are embedded in prose without explicit enumeration, making omission hard to detect. No invariant tests verify that selectors and the missing-governing path work correctly.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go (or prompts package): the shared blocks (extracted by ddx-e2171a2c, a dep) are prose paragraphs averaging ~25 words each. Equivalent checklists would cut to ~10 words per guardrail.\u0026#xA;- No FEAT-022-referencing comment block exists that enumerates all 19 guardrails inline.\u0026#xA;- No invariant tests exist for prompt selectors (which harness-specific block is chosen) or missing-governing path (behavior when governing doc is absent).\u0026#xA;- ddx-e2171a2c (shared block extraction, a dep) must land first.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;- Tighten shared blocks: convert prose paragraphs to bullet checklists targeting \u0026gt;= 30% word reduction on both Claude and Agent variants (~400 words saved on Claude, ~450 on Agent).\u0026#xA;- Verify all 19 guardrails preserved: enumerate each guardrail in a comment or test.\u0026#xA;- Add FEAT-022-referencing comment block listing all 19 guardrails inline (with FEAT-022 cross-reference).\u0026#xA;- Add invariant tests:\u0026#xA;  - TestPromptSelector_CorrectBlock: verifies each harness gets its specific block.\u0026#xA;  - TestPromptSelector_MissingGoverning: verifies missing-governing path uses fallback or errors predictably.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;- Changing prompt semantics or dropping any of the 19 guardrails.\u0026#xA;- Adding new guardrails (those go in the rubric update).\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. Both prompt variants (Claude + Agent) word count reduced by \u0026gt;= 30% from baseline.\u0026#xA;2. All 19 guardrails preserved: TestPromptGuardrails_AllPresent enumerates and asserts each.\u0026#xA;3. FEAT-022 comment block exists listing all 19 guardrails with cross-reference.\u0026#xA;4. TestPromptSelector_CorrectBlock verifies each harness gets its specific block.\u0026#xA;5. TestPromptSelector_MissingGoverning verifies missing-governing path behavior.\u0026#xA;6. Existing eval suite passes (golden output unchanged beyond word-reduction reformatting).\u0026#xA;7. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/agent/... green.\u0026#xA;8. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:2, story:12, area:agent, kind:feature\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-a61bf8ee\" base-rev=\"b016c55f2eed14df1b4686beb055db9d1b1e7a36\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260512T035137-c0bdf98c\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cnote\u003eNo governing references were pre-resolved. The bead description above is the primary contract. If it names files, specs, or prior beads, read those before editing. Ground decisions in what is already in the repository; do not guess.\u003c/note\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","attempt_id":"20260512T035137-c0bdf98c","base_rev":"b016c55f2eed14df1b4686beb055db9d1b1e7a36","bead_id":"ddx-fcdbc731","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260512T035137-c0bdf98c","correlation_id":"ddx-fcdbc731:20260512T035137-c0bdf98c","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260512T035137-c0bdf98c/prompt.md","prompt_sha":"9a69a659f2604380aa704e1c807b37c54797e7ca155c6de1ecd678e73c00bee2","role":"implementer","session_id":"eb-715c9ebc","worker_id":""}}}
